    "However, development and application of NLP to the design of structural alloys are still in early stages.",
    "Sample research includes the text-mining of millions of papers to efficiently design high-entropy alloys [17] as well as predicting the pitting potential for corrosionresistant alloy design using embeddings of literature excerpts [18].",
    "Relevant to aluminum, Liu et al.",
    "have created a labeled dataset of material entities from the literature focused on the Al-Si alloy system [19].",
    "Their use of active learning to supplement their manual labeling of entities, however, highlights the need for an automated high-throughput extraction method applicable to different regions of the alloy space."
